---
title: Za'atar-Crusted Goat Cheese with a Farro, Arugula, and Carrot Salad
description: Za’atar is an ingredient that’s used throughout the Middle East. But its flavor and fragrance—rich with oregano, sesame, and sumac—fit in across cuisines. It’s a perfect match for this salad, in which goat cheese rounds are crusted in its herbs and spices and then placed atop a wholesome combination of farro, carrot ribbons, arugula, and a citrus tahini dressing.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/zaatar-crusted-goat-cheese-9257138f.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/zaatar-crusted-goat-cheese-5abd47faae08b54a9864bbb2-68f4f41b.pdf
course: main course
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: Mediterranean
servings: 2
time required: 30 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 590 kcal
  fat: 27 g
  saturated fat: 7 g
  carbohydrates: 80 g
  sugar: 27 g
  protein: 19 g
  fiber: 17 g
  sodium: 550 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/zaatar-crusted-goat-cheese-5abd47faae08b54a9864bbb2
---

Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to upper position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Peel and halve @shallot{1}. Mince one half; thinly slice other half.

Stir together 3 cups water, @farro{1/2%cup}, minced shallot, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and a few large pinches of @salt{} in a #medium pot{}. Bring to a boil, then lower heat slightly and bring to a rapid simmer. Cook, uncovered, until tender, ~{30-35%minutes}. Drain any excess water. Season with salt and @pepper{}.

Meanwhile, peel @carrots{12%oz}. Slice half the carrots crosswise into ¼-inch-thick coins, then toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{}, 1 1/2 tsp @za'atar spice{} (we'll use the rest later), and a large pinch of salt and pepper. Roast in oven until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Shave remaining carrots lengthwise into ribbons using a #vegetable peeler{}.

On a #small plate{}, mix remaining @za'atar spice{} and 1 1/2 tsp @sesame seeds{} (save the rest for garnish). Gently press @goat cheese{2%oz} rounds into mixture, coating all over. Set aside.

Zest 1 tsp zest from @lemon{1}, then cut into halves. Squeeze 2 TBSP juice into a large #bowl{}. Add zest, 1 TBSP @olive oil{1%tbsp}, @tahini{1%oz}, @honey{1/2%oz}, and 1 TBSP warm water and whisk until combined. Season with salt and pepper.

> If the dressing is thick, add more warm water, 1 tsp at a time, until it reaches a drizzly consistency.

Add @arugula{2%oz}, drained farro, roasted carrots, carrot ribbons, sliced shallot (to taste), and remaining @sesame seeds{1/2%tbsp} to bowl with dressing and toss to combine. Season with salt and pepper. Divide between #bowls{} or #plates{}, top with goat cheese, and serve.